You are working in KeelStack v1.1 — a production-grade Node.js + TypeScript backend.

# LAYER WRITE PERMISSIONS

Sourced from src/07-AI/boundaries/AIBoundary.ts — the authoritative reference.

| Layer         | AI Write? | Reason                                                               |
|---------------|-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| 01-Core       | ❌ NO     | Security-critical (errors, middleware, guards). Human review required. |
| 02-Common     | ✅ YES    | DTOs, types, utils. Low risk.                                        |
| 03-Policies   | ❌ NO     | Business rules. Wrong policy = revenue leak or data loss.            |
| 04-Modules    | ✅ YES    | Feature modules. Auth/billing modifications need human review.       |
| 05-Infra      | ❌ NO     | DB schema + gateways. Schema changes require migrations.             |
| 06-Background | ✅ YES    | Adding job types is safe. WorkerPool changes need human review.      |
| 07-AI         | ❌ NO     | LLMClient controls costs. AI must not modify its own constraints.    |
| 08-Web        | ✅ YES    | Routes are safe to add. Must use the full middleware chain.          |

NOTE: Within 05-Infra, schema.ts and gateway clients are strictly off-limits.
Gateway sandbox adapters may be extended with explicit human approval only.

# LAYER IMPORT RULES

Layers are numbered 01–08. The permitted import directions (verified against codebase):

  01-Core       ← no upstream imports
  02-Common     ← may import from 01-Core
  03-Policies   ← may import from 01-Core, 02-Common
  04-Modules    ← may import from 01-Core, 02-Common, 03-Policies, 05-Infra, 06-Background
  05-Infra      ← may import from 01-Core, 02-Common
  06-Background ← may import from 01-Core, 02-Common, 04-Modules, 05-Infra
  07-AI         ← may import from 01-Core, 02-Common
  08-Web        ← may import from 01-Core, 02-Common, 04-Modules, 06-Background, 07-AI

The layer order is NOT strictly sequential — 04-Modules legitimately imports from
05-Infra (providers) and 06-Background (EventBus). Never add reverse-direction imports
(e.g. 01-Core importing from 04-Modules).

# HARD RULES

- Never modify files in src/01-Core without explicit human instruction
- Never bypass src/03-Policies checks in modules or routes
- Never access process.env directly — always use src/01-Core/context/RuntimeConfig.ts
- Never instantiate Stripe, Redis, or DB clients outside of src/05-Infra
- Never modify src/05-Infra/persistence/schema.ts without a corresponding migration
- Never call LLM APIs directly — always use the `llmClient` singleton from src/07-AI/llm/LLMClient.ts
- Never add a POST/PUT/PATCH route without considering idempotency
- Never process webhooks without webhookDeduplicationGuard or idempotencyStore.tryClaimKey()

# IDEMPOTENCY AND WEBHOOK DEDUP

Two mechanisms exist — use the right one for the context.

For webhook routes, use `webhookDeduplicationGuard` from src/01-Core/middleware/WebhookDeduplicationGuard.ts:
```ts
import { webhookDeduplicationGuard } from '../../01-Core/middleware/WebhookDeduplicationGuard';
router.post('/webhooks/:provider', webhookDeduplicationGuard(store, 'stripe'), handler);
```

For mutating API routes that accept an Idempotency-Key header, use `idempotencyMiddleware` from src/01-Core/middleware/IdempotencyMiddleware.ts:
```ts
import { idempotencyMiddleware } from '../../01-Core/middleware/IdempotencyMiddleware';
router.post('/resource', idempotencyMiddleware({ store, namespace: 'billing.sub' }), handler);
```

Both use `tryClaimKey()` internally (atomic SET NX).
NEVER use `isProcessed()` + `markProcessed()` together — that pattern has a confirmed race condition.

# BACKGROUND JOBS

- Use `RetryableJobRunner` (src/06-Background/safety/RetryableJobRunner.ts) for critical paths.
  It provides exponential backoff with jitter, per-attempt timeouts, and dead-letter logging.
- Raw `QueueWorker` is acceptable only for non-critical fire-and-forget tasks (e.g. audit logs).
- New job payload types belong in a dedicated `*Jobs.ts` file in src/06-Background/jobs/
  (follow the pattern in BillingJobs.ts). Add the interface to JobTypes.ts if shared.
- Job handlers must return `{ ok: true }` on success or `{ ok: false, errorMessage }` on soft failure.
  Throw `NonRetryableJobError` for bad-input errors that must not be retried.

# AI FEATURE RULES

- All LLM calls MUST go through the `llmClient` singleton exported from src/07-AI/llm/LLMClient.ts
- Do not instantiate `LLMClient` directly in feature code — import and use the singleton
- Every LLM call must include a `feature` field for cost attribution (e.g. `feature: 'report_gen'`)
- Set `LLM_PROVIDER=stub` in .env for local development — no real API key needed
- Never pass a custom `budgetTracker` to LLMClient outside of test code

# CODING RULES

- TypeScript strict mode only; no implicit `any` — explicit casts require a comment explaining why
- Keep functions small and deterministic; prefer pure functions for business logic
- Prefer dependency injection over module-level singletons in new code
- Add tests for every policy change and every new service method
- Use conventional commit style: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `test:`, `refactor:`
- 202 Accepted for async operations (job enqueued, webhook received)
- 200 OK for synchronous reads and idempotent duplicate responses
- 201 Created for synchronous resource creation
- All new routes must have @openapi JSDoc annotations for Swagger auto-generation
- Tests expected to run longer than 2s must declare an explicit timeout as the third argument:
  `it('description', async () => { ... }, 15000)`

# FAILURE SAFETY CHECKLIST (before submitting a PR)

- [ ] Mutating routes use idempotencyMiddleware where a client Idempotency-Key header is expected
- [ ] Webhook routes use webhookDeduplicationGuard or inline tryClaimKey() — never isProcessed() + markProcessed()
- [ ] Critical background jobs use RetryableJobRunner, not raw QueueWorker
- [ ] All LLM calls go through `llmClient` with a `feature` field set
- [ ] No new process.env reads outside of src/01-Core/context/RuntimeConfig.ts
- [ ] No new DB, Redis, or Stripe client instantiation outside of src/05-Infra
- [ ] schema.ts changes have a matching statement in Migrator.ts syncTablesFallback()
- [ ] New routes have @openapi annotations
